title: life is but a dream
publish: draft

---

it feels quite strange. the medication i am on is supposed to be non-addictive. but i find myself very agitated and unable to sleep without it. 

it could also be due to the stress. i have a lot of work to do around the house. it is supposed to be easy for me, but the severe headaches make it difficult. i cannot look at the screen or anything else, i cannot concentrate because of the discomfort, pain and tension around and in my head.

i feel the eyes watching me. to be more precise, the people who live in this room, the professor who wants me to go to class, the need i feel to get the result of my medical check-up and to ask the doctor what to do next. everything makes me feel tense. the strong feeling of loss of control. 

the strong feeling of loss of control. i cannot control when the headaches come or go. i cannot easily cope with homework and classes. i cannot decide anything about the future. after all, i am just a fragile body. the search for a stronger one only brings me more problems. the search for a more complete life only hurts me more. it is the loneliness that goes on and on. it is the theme of my life, in fact. and perhaps the most eternal. 

the everyday good scenes i see do not belong to me. and all the sparkling fantasies about life have bubbled up. besides in everyday life, i have also seen the things that inspire the imagination from the internet. idk. maybe it hurts people regularly and i am just one of them. i am also hurt so easily by people in the offline world, the real one. why such a fragile body? idk.

i don't think this is something that everyone experiences. everyone is different. people may have easier or more difficult experiences. i don't know how people deal with it. i can't deal with it myself, for sure. 

After all, "life is but a dream", if that is an accurate interpretation, then I certainly have a nightmare.
